539.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vur1665703193539.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/vur1665703193539.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"vur1665703193539\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Logon as a privileged administrative user of the Uniface Router.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"vur1665703193539__topic_d134942e1_d134943e1_d134944e1\">\n<p class=\"lines\" id=\"vur1665703193539__lines_irn_cyc_gwb\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">operation ADMLOGON</code><br/><code class=\"ph codeph\">params</code><br/><code class=\"ph codeph\">  string</code> <var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var> <code class=\"ph codeph\">: IN ; (C40)</code><br/><code class=\"ph codeph\">  string</code> <var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var> <code class=\"ph codeph\">: IN ; (C40)</code><br/><code class=\"ph codeph\">endparams</code></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vur1665703193539__section_zt3_myc_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d441114e82\">Parameters</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"vur1665703193539__ul_h5x_nyc_gwb\">\n<li class=\"li\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">User</var>—user account under which the Uniface Router runs, as specified\n          by the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$PRIV_MON_USER</span> assignment setting; if it is not specified, the\n          default account is assumed to be <code class=\"ph codeph\">urouter</code>; For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prv1665702740862.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prv1665702740862.html\" title=\"Specify the privileged user account under which the Uniface Router runs and which can be used to start and stop Uniface Routers and Servers using the Uniface Router Monitor or the UROUTMON component.\">$PRIV_MON_USER</a>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>—password for the user name.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vur1665703193539__section_tkm_pyc_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d441114e114\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">If successful, <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span> is set to 0. Otherwise, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qln1665702528769.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qln1665702528769.html#qln1665702528769__section_fbt_4d2_gwb\">Return Codes</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vur1665703193539__section_gf1_tyc_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d441114e130\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Allowed in all Uniface component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"vur1665703193539__section_ypb_5yc_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d441114e139\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The <span class=\"keyword apiname\">ADMLOGON</span> operation is used to log on as privileged administrative\n        user of the Uniface Router. If successful, privileged operations are allowed, such as\n        starting and stopping Uniface Routers and Uniface Servers.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2533186\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "ADMLOGON Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Logon as a privileged administrative user of the Uniface Router. operation ADMLOGON params string User : IN ; (C40) string Password : IN ; (C40) endparams Parameters User —user account under which the Uniface Router runs, as specified by the $PRIV_MON_USER assignment setting; if it is not specified, the default account is assumed to be urouter ; For more information, see $PRIV_MON_USER . Password —password for the user name. Return Values If successful, $status is set to 0. Otherwise, see Return Codes . Use Allowed in all Uniface component types. Description The ADMLOGON operation is used to log on as privileged administrative user of the Uniface Router. If successful, privileged operations are allowed, such as starting and stopping Uniface Routers and Uniface Servers. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}